WEBVTT

00:02.273 --> 00:04.573
Attention, citizens of the Internet.

00:04.575 --> 00:07.709
We are calling upon
every able-bodied viewer

00:07.711 --> 00:11.564
for another adrenalized
tour of duty for Shay's Army.

00:11.566 --> 00:12.789
I am General Shay.

00:12.791 --> 00:14.382
And I am Major Mitch.

00:14.384 --> 00:16.283
- And I'm Jess...
- Shut the hell up, Jessie.

00:16.286 --> 00:17.752
Seriously, no one's gonna recognize you.

00:17.754 --> 00:19.654
Not without a microwave
cemented on your head.

00:19.656 --> 00:22.023
We're coming to you
live from Hacienda Park

00:22.025 --> 00:24.993
where we have a stunt so daring...

00:24.995 --> 00:27.195
A video so bold...

00:27.197 --> 00:28.669
- It might...
- Just...

00:28.671 --> 00:30.871
Break the Internet!

00:30.873 --> 00:34.207
We're about to turn
this merry-go-round...

00:34.209 --> 00:36.810
Into a scary-go-round.

00:38.147 --> 00:40.313
Oh.

00:40.315 --> 00:43.249
Daddy likes. Whoo!

00:43.251 --> 00:44.684
Jessie, you ready to take a ride

00:44.686 --> 00:47.383
into infinity and beyond?

00:47.385 --> 00:48.474
Perfect.

00:48.476 --> 00:51.404
- Ready, set...
- Spin.

00:59.400 --> 01:01.033
Look at him go. It's beautiful.

01:11.645 --> 01:14.246
Oh, you're really burning rubber.

01:18.519 --> 01:20.352
- Whoa!
- Oh. Oh.

01:20.354 --> 01:22.287
Yo, shut him down, man.

01:29.463 --> 01:31.062
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

01:31.064 --> 01:32.130
Not again!

01:32.132 --> 01:33.665
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

01:34.470 --> 01:36.092
_

01:36.094 --> 01:40.410
_

01:40.412 --> 01:42.375
_

01:44.778 --> 01:47.446
So what, now they
got self-driving motorcycles?

01:47.448 --> 01:48.937
Wouldn't that defeat the point?

01:48.939 --> 01:50.261
That rider couldn't have gone far.

01:50.263 --> 01:52.851
Buck, Eddie, hose that
down and turn that bike off.

01:57.957 --> 01:59.156
Think I saw Christopher

01:59.158 --> 02:01.191
watching a video like this online.

02:01.193 --> 02:03.127
That bike wasn't on fire.

02:03.129 --> 02:04.795
Hey, can you hear me?

02:04.797 --> 02:06.130
Oh! Oh.

02:06.132 --> 02:07.331
Uh...

02:07.333 --> 02:08.853
All right, let's get him off of there.

02:15.642 --> 02:17.475
His pupils are extremely dilated.

02:17.477 --> 02:19.977
Globe luxation in both eyes

02:19.979 --> 02:21.312
causing them to bulge out.

02:21.314 --> 02:22.846
Blood pressure's off the charts.

02:22.848 --> 02:25.216
- Starting a line.
- Albert, what happened to him?

02:25.218 --> 02:26.317
Depending on how many times

02:26.319 --> 02:28.152
he was spinning around like
that, it could be G-lock.

02:28.154 --> 02:30.032
G-force poisoning from
the force of the spin?

02:30.034 --> 02:32.790
Right now, all his blood
is pooling inside his head.

02:32.792 --> 02:34.024
It's pressing against his brain.

02:34.026 --> 02:35.693
That's why he's out cold.

02:35.695 --> 02:37.968
We don't get that swelling
down, he could have a stroke.

02:37.970 --> 02:40.164
We've gotta get him stable
enough for transport.

02:40.166 --> 02:42.239
Running isotonic fluids.

02:42.241 --> 02:44.675
Wait, I feel like I know this guy.

02:44.677 --> 02:46.777
All right, BP's stabilizing.

02:46.779 --> 02:48.545
Administering numbing drops.

02:48.547 --> 02:50.380
I'll hold back the curtains

02:50.382 --> 02:53.951
while you show these
guests to their seats.

02:53.953 --> 02:57.221
All right.

02:57.223 --> 02:59.656
Here you go.

03:07.161 --> 03:08.516
Cap, we're good here.

03:08.518 --> 03:10.090
All right, let's get
him up and transported

03:10.092 --> 03:12.436
to the nearest
neurosurgery trauma center.

03:12.438 --> 03:14.939
I can see. Thank you.

03:14.941 --> 03:16.140
Who did this to you?

03:18.009 --> 03:19.109
Oh, I have an idea.

03:22.380 --> 03:25.181
You think Jessie's okay?
He looks really messed up.

03:25.183 --> 03:26.616
I'm sure he's fine.

03:26.618 --> 03:28.384
Maybe we should go to the hospital.

03:28.386 --> 03:30.887
Afraid you're gonna be
otherwise occupied.

03:30.889 --> 03:34.023
You're under arrest for
trespassing, vandalism,

03:34.025 --> 03:37.326
reckless endangerment,
and disturbing the peace.

03:37.328 --> 03:39.129
- You can't prove anything.
- Don't need to.

03:39.131 --> 03:42.639
You fools livestreamed your
confession on the Internet.

03:42.641 --> 03:44.067
Hey, guys. Remember us?

03:44.069 --> 03:46.522
You've gotta be kidding
me. How small is this town?

03:46.524 --> 03:48.438
Don't think you're posting
that without our permission.

03:48.439 --> 03:50.073
Yeah, even if you did,

03:50.075 --> 03:51.507
just gonna get us more followers.

03:51.509 --> 03:53.243
Nah, this is just for
an audience of one.

03:56.681 --> 04:00.182
Man, I really need new friends.

04:13.184 --> 04:16.184
- Synced and corrected by<font color="#00BFFF"> Firefly</font> -
- <font color="#00ffff">www.addic7ed.com</font> -

04:18.935 --> 04:20.303
Oh, I know that smile.

04:21.406 --> 04:23.172
Pair of aces.

04:30.281 --> 04:31.480
Flush.

04:31.482 --> 04:33.349
- Oh!
- Yes!

04:33.351 --> 04:34.550
He falls for it every time.

04:34.552 --> 04:36.184
How does this keep on happening?

04:36.186 --> 04:37.819
Because you suck at poker.

04:37.821 --> 04:40.355
Spoken by someone who
also sucks at poker.

04:40.357 --> 04:42.757
No judgment, but maybe you
should quit while you're behind.

04:42.759 --> 04:44.025
Wow.

04:44.027 --> 04:46.361
Who needs more wine? Kay.

04:46.363 --> 04:48.029
I'm gonna need something stronger.

04:48.031 --> 04:50.131
Thanks again for
having me. This was fun.

04:50.133 --> 04:51.700
For some of us.

04:51.702 --> 04:53.267
Well, all our couple friends were busy,

04:53.269 --> 04:55.437
so we figured we would target solos.

04:55.439 --> 04:58.005
If I didn't know better, I'd
say you were setting us up.

04:58.007 --> 05:00.174
Oh, no, I like you way too much
to set you up with my brother.

05:00.176 --> 05:01.209
Uh, hey now.

05:01.211 --> 05:02.977
And I love you too much

05:02.979 --> 05:04.646
to let you keep being

05:04.648 --> 05:08.015
so incredibly, tragically...

05:08.017 --> 05:09.651
Some might say embarrassingly.

05:09.653 --> 05:11.152
Single.

05:11.154 --> 05:12.687
Tragic seems a bit much.

05:12.689 --> 05:14.356
Closest you've gotten
to turning on a woman

05:14.358 --> 05:16.980
in the past few months is
shouting out, "Hey, Siri!"

05:16.982 --> 05:18.425
Well, she's very good to me.

05:18.427 --> 05:20.719
She sings me songs,
she delivers me food,

05:20.721 --> 05:23.611
she tells me where to be,
when, and how to get there,

05:23.613 --> 05:24.879
and that is pretty much love.

05:24.881 --> 05:26.581
- The rest I...
- Ew, no!

05:26.583 --> 05:28.316
Oh, no, no, no. Dear
God, I don't wanna know.

05:28.318 --> 05:31.153
All right, all right,
just ease up on the solos.

05:31.155 --> 05:32.254
It's hard out here.

05:32.256 --> 05:33.922
See? Thank you.

05:33.924 --> 05:35.323
It's LA.

05:35.325 --> 05:37.526
Everybody's always in their car

05:37.528 --> 05:39.794
or looking at their phones.

05:39.796 --> 05:41.342
Or in their car looking at their phones.

05:41.344 --> 05:43.365
And we're stuck with
online dating, which is...

05:43.367 --> 05:44.566
An absolute nightmare.

05:44.568 --> 05:46.868
The crazies, the randos, the catfishers,

05:46.870 --> 05:48.836
and not to mention the liars.

05:48.838 --> 05:52.374
Profile pics brought
to you by Photoshop.

05:52.376 --> 05:54.609
Face it, guys. You two got lucky.

05:54.611 --> 05:55.700
They did.

05:55.702 --> 05:59.281
You guys have no idea
how hard it is out there

05:59.283 --> 06:01.015
for the solos.

06:02.418 --> 06:04.251
Mm.

06:04.253 --> 06:05.620
Where's Albert tonight?

06:07.857 --> 06:10.858
He's on a date.

06:10.860 --> 06:12.493
Come on.

06:12.495 --> 06:14.028
Perfect.

06:14.030 --> 06:18.032
Looking for room 203.

06:19.603 --> 06:23.571
Didn't it just go from 201 to 205?

06:23.573 --> 06:25.334
Oh, it's the next one on the left.

06:25.336 --> 06:28.109
Lab classrooms have a different layout.

06:28.111 --> 06:30.812
Of course they do. Thank
you again for coming.

06:30.814 --> 06:32.213
Don't know if I'd be able to navigate

06:32.215 --> 06:33.948
the confusing waters
of parent-teacher night

06:33.950 --> 06:34.983
without you.

06:34.985 --> 06:37.118
Well, knowing these
things is sorta my job.

06:37.120 --> 06:38.820
Okay, follow my lead.

06:38.822 --> 06:41.155
Try to ignore these
teachers' corny jokes.

06:42.959 --> 06:44.058
What jokes?

06:44.060 --> 06:46.260
What do you call a number
that won't sit still?

06:48.063 --> 06:49.563
A roamin' numeral.

06:53.836 --> 06:55.603
How do you make a bandstand?

06:55.605 --> 06:58.239
Take away their chairs!

06:59.475 --> 07:01.308
I don't think he got it.

07:01.310 --> 07:04.044
No, I... I did.

07:04.046 --> 07:06.380
Christopher shows a
great interest in science,

07:06.382 --> 07:08.849
though he does keep
telling other students

07:08.851 --> 07:11.785
tsunamis aren't a big
deal, which is unhelpful.

07:11.787 --> 07:14.321
I'll make sure to
talk to him about that.

07:14.323 --> 07:16.190
Thank you.

07:18.994 --> 07:20.027
No jokes?

07:21.464 --> 07:23.397
I try to tell chemistry jokes,

07:23.399 --> 07:25.098
but there's no reaction.

07:26.001 --> 07:28.834
Get it? No reaction?

07:30.038 --> 07:32.305
Ah, you weren't kidding about the jokes.

07:32.307 --> 07:36.075
Well, hopefully the English
teacher has a better shtick.

07:36.077 --> 07:37.777
So sorry to keep you waiting.

07:37.779 --> 07:39.212
My last student's father asked

07:39.214 --> 07:40.746
a surprising amount of questions.

07:40.748 --> 07:42.081
I'm sure he did.

07:42.083 --> 07:43.849
Good to see you again, Ms. Price.

07:43.851 --> 07:45.285
And you must be Mr. Diaz.

07:45.287 --> 07:47.487
Please, call me Eddie. It's short for...

07:47.489 --> 07:49.322
Edmundo?

07:49.324 --> 07:50.790
Most people guess Eduardo.

07:50.792 --> 07:53.693
Growing up, I had a
grandfather named Edmundo.

07:53.695 --> 07:55.109
He was my favorite.

07:55.111 --> 07:57.564
Mine too. I mean...

07:57.566 --> 07:59.732
So let's talk about Christopher.

07:59.734 --> 08:01.734
He's been doing really well in my class.

08:01.736 --> 08:04.070
His verbal skills have
definitely improved.

08:04.072 --> 08:06.606
He's still a little shy
about reading out loud,

08:06.608 --> 08:09.074
but he definitely
understands the material.

08:09.076 --> 08:11.543
I attribute that to him being
read to from an early age,

08:11.545 --> 08:13.212
so bravo there.

08:13.214 --> 08:15.647
No, we have his mother
to thank for that.

08:15.649 --> 08:17.583
Christopher tells me you've kept it up

08:17.585 --> 08:19.418
since she's been gone.

08:19.420 --> 08:22.047
I try to do the voices,
but she was better at it.

08:22.049 --> 08:23.604
Oh, I'm sure you're no slouch.

08:23.606 --> 08:24.895
Oh, no, he isn't.

08:26.588 --> 08:29.628
Christopher is also one of
our most popular students.

08:29.630 --> 08:31.763
He loves making the other kids laugh.

08:31.765 --> 08:33.332
- Is that a problem?
- Not at all.

08:33.333 --> 08:35.933
He's a very sweet and kind boy.

08:35.936 --> 08:37.369
You're doing a great job.

08:38.438 --> 08:39.770
Thank you.

08:43.744 --> 08:45.977
We gonna talk about that?

08:45.979 --> 08:49.948
That I'm basically raising a
funny, popular, young genius?

08:49.950 --> 08:52.650
That has a pretty young
thing for an English teacher.

08:52.652 --> 08:54.618
Was she pretty? Didn't even notice.

08:54.620 --> 08:55.786
Oh, I'm sorry.

08:55.788 --> 08:57.287
I must have you confused with someone

08:57.289 --> 09:00.290
who couldn't stop gazing into
Ms. Flores's big blue eyes.

09:00.292 --> 09:01.625
They were brown.

09:01.627 --> 09:02.860
And you're right.

09:02.862 --> 09:04.394
Too bad you didn't notice.

09:11.203 --> 09:12.970
Paging Dr. Becker.

09:12.972 --> 09:14.772
Paging Dr. Becker.

09:17.309 --> 09:18.742
Dr. Calloway.

09:18.744 --> 09:20.510
Sergeant Grant. Good to see you.

09:20.512 --> 09:23.413
- How's your husband?
- Bobby's doing well, thank you.

09:23.415 --> 09:24.815
You called in a gunshot wound?

09:24.817 --> 09:26.984
Yes. Female, early 50s.

09:26.986 --> 09:28.886
Came in complaining about headaches

09:28.888 --> 09:30.520
and some disorientation.

09:30.522 --> 09:33.856
Now, given the scar tissue,

09:33.858 --> 09:35.825
I'm going to estimate
this bullet has been there

09:35.827 --> 09:37.994
for two, maybe three months.

09:37.996 --> 09:41.164
Wait. This is an old gunshot wound?

09:41.166 --> 09:42.198
Yes.

09:42.200 --> 09:44.267
Why wasn't it reported
the day it happened?

09:44.269 --> 09:47.370
Because that woman didn't
even know she had been shot.

09:47.372 --> 09:48.805
Not until today.

09:57.699 --> 09:59.198
Joan?

09:59.200 --> 10:01.100
This is Detective Romero.

10:01.102 --> 10:02.268
He needs to ask you...

10:02.270 --> 10:04.070
More questions?

10:04.072 --> 10:07.425
I really think this has
to be a terrible mistake.

10:07.427 --> 10:09.641
I promise you I have never been shot.

10:09.643 --> 10:12.477
In the head or anywhere else.

10:12.479 --> 10:15.398
It feels like something I'd
remember, don't you think?

10:15.400 --> 10:17.248
Ma'am, we saw the X-rays.

10:17.250 --> 10:20.452
So did I. And Dr...

10:20.454 --> 10:24.189
- Calloway.
- Yes, Dr. Calloway.

10:24.191 --> 10:26.388
He seems like a lovely man,

10:26.390 --> 10:28.657
but hospitals always make mistakes.

10:28.659 --> 10:31.127
I've heard stories about people

10:31.129 --> 10:33.162
having the wrong limbs amputated.

10:33.164 --> 10:34.912
Well, the doctor seems pretty sure,

10:34.914 --> 10:36.404
so we need to investigate,

10:36.406 --> 10:38.167
find out what might've happened to you.

10:38.169 --> 10:40.369
So the doctor thinks
that if you were shot,

10:40.371 --> 10:42.371
it would've happened
sometime in January,

10:42.373 --> 10:43.522
maybe early February.

10:43.524 --> 10:45.673
Did anything during
that time period happen

10:45.675 --> 10:47.342
that was unusual?

10:47.344 --> 10:50.511
Not really. My life is pretty boring.

10:50.513 --> 10:53.381
It's just me and my husband.

10:53.383 --> 10:55.083
Where is your husband? Is he on his way?

10:55.085 --> 10:57.853
No, he's out of town. Golfing I think.

10:57.855 --> 11:00.553
Maybe Pebble Beach.

11:00.555 --> 11:02.378
He took early retirement last year,

11:02.380 --> 11:04.459
so he is always looking
for things to do.

11:04.461 --> 11:07.262
Me, I am a happy homebody.

11:07.264 --> 11:09.697
I should call him, shouldn't I?

11:09.699 --> 11:11.766
Oh, you know,

11:11.768 --> 11:14.769
I probably have the information in here.

11:18.075 --> 11:21.576
Joan, you came into
the ER with a headache.

11:21.578 --> 11:22.967
Do you get those a lot?

11:22.969 --> 11:25.747
Never used to, but now it
seems like I always have one.

11:25.749 --> 11:28.449
I tried cutting out caffeine

11:28.451 --> 11:31.586
and red wine and bacon, but still.

11:31.588 --> 11:33.654
Oh, here.

11:33.656 --> 11:34.756
Thank you.

11:36.393 --> 11:38.959
Do you normally write everything down?

11:38.961 --> 11:41.729
Always prided myself
in remembering things.

11:41.731 --> 11:44.932
Names, phone numbers, birthdays.

11:44.934 --> 11:46.200
But you get older,

11:46.202 --> 11:49.336
and you start to need a little help.

11:49.338 --> 11:52.172
- Joan, are you okay?
- Ooh.

11:52.174 --> 11:57.845
I think I need to talk to
that doctor again, um...

11:57.847 --> 12:00.047
- Dr...
- Calloway?

12:00.049 --> 12:03.116
Yes, thank you. Oh,
my memory is terrible.

12:03.118 --> 12:04.951
Do you mind if we keep
this? We'll return it.

12:04.953 --> 12:06.787
Oh, go right ahead.

12:06.789 --> 12:07.888
- Thank you.
- Thank you, Joan.

12:07.890 --> 12:08.988
Mm.

12:14.062 --> 12:15.796
She really doesn't remember being shot.

12:15.798 --> 12:17.196
I'm not sure she wants to.

12:17.198 --> 12:19.966
You think it's the husband.

12:19.968 --> 12:22.869
I think that no one ever really knows

12:22.871 --> 12:25.138
what goes on inside of a marriage.

12:25.140 --> 12:28.041
Sometimes, not even
the people inside it.

12:34.348 --> 12:35.348
Carla.

12:36.193 --> 12:37.381
What the hell happened?

12:37.383 --> 12:38.851
I told you Christopher is fine.

12:38.853 --> 12:40.018
You didn't have to come down here.

12:40.020 --> 12:41.119
It's just some scrapes and bruises.

12:41.121 --> 12:43.422
He hurt himself? How?

12:43.424 --> 12:45.825
Well, it turns out that
Christopher and skateboards

12:45.827 --> 12:47.015
don't get along very well.

12:47.017 --> 12:50.295
- You let him skateboard?
- I am so sorry, Mr. Diaz.

12:50.297 --> 12:52.297
We didn't know one of the
kids had brought a skateboard.

12:52.299 --> 12:53.766
You didn't know?

12:53.768 --> 12:54.834
He could've broken his neck.

12:54.836 --> 12:57.470
I know, and I feel terrible.

12:57.472 --> 12:59.872
The other kids were
showing him how to ride it

12:59.874 --> 13:01.593
- and they didn't know that...
- Didn't they?

13:01.595 --> 13:04.550
No, let's push the kid with CP
around on a skateboard for fun.

13:04.552 --> 13:06.174
You let them make a fool out of my son.

13:06.176 --> 13:07.433
Eddie.

13:07.435 --> 13:10.247
I promise you that's
not what happened here.

13:12.418 --> 13:14.285
Christopher. Hey.

13:15.822 --> 13:17.455
Oh, my God.

13:17.457 --> 13:19.056
Are you okay?

13:19.058 --> 13:21.626
I'm sorry about my clothes.

13:21.628 --> 13:22.760
No, don't worry about that.

13:22.762 --> 13:24.095
I could run to the house,

13:24.097 --> 13:25.697
get some clean clothes
for him to change into.

13:25.699 --> 13:27.298
No, we're done for the day.

13:27.300 --> 13:29.868
Come on. We're leaving.

13:29.870 --> 13:32.403
But school isn't over.

13:32.405 --> 13:34.405
It is now.

13:40.713 --> 13:42.046
Uh-huh.

13:45.684 --> 13:48.619
Well, I appreciate
that, Principal Summers.

13:48.621 --> 13:51.088
Okay. Thank you.

13:51.090 --> 13:53.724
So should I expect some
kid's head on a spike

13:53.726 --> 13:54.925
at tomorrow's drop-off?

13:54.927 --> 13:56.360
They sent skateboard kid home early.

13:56.362 --> 13:58.262
Principal's gonna meet with
the parents in the morning,

13:58.264 --> 13:59.530
figure out what the
punishment should be.

13:59.532 --> 14:02.433
And what about the kid who
fell off the skateboard?

14:02.435 --> 14:04.235
Think I should punish
Christopher for getting hurt?

14:04.237 --> 14:05.469
No,

14:05.471 --> 14:06.803
but I think you should talk to him

14:06.805 --> 14:08.805
about how he got hurt.

14:08.807 --> 14:12.009
I know Christopher wants to be
like all the other kids, but...

14:12.011 --> 14:13.109
You want me to tell him he's different?

14:13.111 --> 14:15.512
He already knows that.

14:15.514 --> 14:18.214
You need to teach him what it means.

14:19.785 --> 14:22.152
That he has limitations.

14:24.924 --> 14:26.990
I'm not gonna tell my kid that.

14:29.479 --> 14:32.396
Hey, buddy. How you feeling?

14:32.398 --> 14:33.496
Dumb.

14:33.498 --> 14:36.166
What? What are you talking about?

14:36.168 --> 14:39.069
Everybody saw me fall.

14:39.071 --> 14:42.238
People fall. It happens.

14:42.240 --> 14:44.473
Nothing to be embarrassed about.

14:44.475 --> 14:46.776
Mm-hmm, that boy should've
never pressured you

14:46.778 --> 14:48.210
