who seems sweet and funny

15:34.183 --> 15:36.572
and not at all like one
of those chat room psychos.

15:36.574 --> 15:37.985
Wait, how can you tell?

15:37.987 --> 15:40.921
His profile contains actual sentences

15:40.923 --> 15:43.256
with correct grammar and punctuation.

15:43.258 --> 15:45.509
There was even a successfully
deployed semicolon.

15:45.511 --> 15:48.345
Ugh, I never use semicolons.
I just don't get the point.

15:48.347 --> 15:50.181
Anyway, we're meeting up tonight

15:50.183 --> 15:52.416
in a public setting,

15:52.418 --> 15:54.518
and I am really looking forward to it.

15:54.520 --> 15:56.386
I just...

15:56.388 --> 15:57.922
What?

15:57.924 --> 16:00.724
I don't want the one-night stand.

16:00.726 --> 16:02.659
I'm tired of being alone.

16:02.661 --> 16:04.084
Aside from my coworkers,

16:04.086 --> 16:06.230
the most meaningful
relationships in my life

16:06.232 --> 16:08.265
are made 10 minutes at a time

16:08.267 --> 16:11.035
with people I'll never
see or talk to again,

16:11.037 --> 16:13.837
some of whom don't survive.

16:13.839 --> 16:16.373
It sounds silly, but he calls,

16:16.375 --> 16:18.041
and I'm excited to answer the phone

16:18.043 --> 16:20.377
for the first time in a long time.

16:20.379 --> 16:22.212
I don't think that sounds silly at all.

16:22.214 --> 16:25.515
So you don't think online
dating is a terrible idea?

16:25.517 --> 16:28.284
I think everyone has a match.

16:28.286 --> 16:30.387
You just have to find him.

16:33.892 --> 16:35.959
Hey, guys. Tessa here.

16:35.961 --> 16:38.928
I'm 27 and from the Bay Area.

16:38.930 --> 16:40.564
Full disclosure, I'm a vegan,

16:40.566 --> 16:43.633
