22:02.423 --> 22:04.924
Pretty sure all kids
call their parents liars

22:04.926 --> 22:06.324
at some point.

22:06.326 --> 22:08.620
Yeah, well, feels a little different

22:08.622 --> 22:09.887
when you hear it coming out of your kid.

22:09.889 --> 22:11.423
Just wait till he gets to the

22:11.425 --> 22:13.267
"I don't have to do
what you tell me" phase.

22:13.269 --> 22:15.135
Aren't you still in that phase?

22:15.137 --> 22:16.803
The thing is, he's right.

22:16.805 --> 22:18.338
I lied to him.

22:18.340 --> 22:20.274
Or maybe I lied to myself.

22:20.276 --> 22:22.409
Either way, I feel like a fool.

22:22.411 --> 22:24.811
I spent years trying to convince my kid

22:24.813 --> 22:26.780
to believe in the Easter Bunny.

22:28.550 --> 22:30.717
But now I gotta tell
him none of it's real.

22:30.719 --> 22:33.165
Yeah, I think you might
be overcorrecting here.

22:33.167 --> 22:35.389
Told him he's no different
than the other kid.

22:35.391 --> 22:37.024
But he is. He has CP.

22:38.394 --> 22:39.592
There's a lot he can't do.

22:41.029 --> 22:43.296
Have you ever heard of Jim Abbott?

22:43.298 --> 22:44.697
- Baseball player?
- Mm-hmm.

22:44.699 --> 22:46.299
Pitched a no-hitter in the '90s,

22:46.301 --> 22:48.635
which in itself is pretty crazy,

22:48.637 --> 22:51.003
but it's even crazier

22:51.005 --> 22:54.941
if you know that Jim Abbott
was only born with one hand.

22:54.943 --> 22:56.175
Yeah, really.

22:56.177 --> 22:57.944
I read his book when
I was in the hospital.

22:57.946 --> 22:59.546
Okay.

22:59.548 --> 23:00.947
How'd he do it?

23:00.949 --> 23:03.483
He practiced switching his glove

23:03.485 --> 23:05.919
to his throwing hand relentlessly

23:05.921 --> 23:08.087
so that he could field after he pitched.

23:08.089 --> 23:10.924
I like the positivity.

23:10.926 --> 23:12.759
I'm just not sure how
any amount of practice

23:12.761 --> 23:14.694
is gonna help Chris
stay on a skateboard.

23:24.438 --> 23:26.304
I'm not an invalid, you know.

23:26.306 --> 23:28.740
I can still get groceries for myself.

23:28.742 --> 23:31.109
I'm doing something nice.

23:31.111 --> 23:32.143
Say thank you.

23:32.145 --> 23:33.345
Ooh. Thank you.

23:33.347 --> 23:35.046
Huh. You're welcome.

23:35.048 --> 23:37.950
So what's happening now
with your bullet lady?

23:37.952 --> 23:39.518
They removed the bullet this morning,

23:39.520 --> 23:41.487
so just waiting on ballistics

23:41.489 --> 23:43.856
to give us a clue to something.

23:43.858 --> 23:45.223
Well, what about the husband?

23:47.561 --> 23:50.562
Claims he has no
idea how his wife got shot.

23:50.564 --> 23:52.063
I love you.

23:52.065 --> 23:53.230
I love you too.

23:53.232 --> 23:54.465
I love you more.

23:54.467 --> 23:56.734
He actually tried to interrogate us.

23:56.736 --> 23:58.921
Yeah, the best defense
is a good offense.

23:58.923 --> 24:00.237
What about his alibi?

24:00.239 --> 24:02.573
Well, we don't even
know when she was shot.

24:02.575 --> 24:04.809
I mean, without a specific timeline,

24:04.811 --> 24:06.259
we can't prove anything.

24:06.261 --> 24:09.480
And the wife still doesn't
suspect him at all?

24:09.482 --> 24:11.983
They say love is blind.

24:11.985 --> 24:14.616
But in this case, I think willfully so.

24:16.589 --> 24:18.923
I mean, she went from
having a great memory

24:18.925 --> 24:20.491
to forgetting the name of the doctor

24:20.493 --> 24:22.259
that she met an hour ago.

24:22.261 --> 24:24.194
Never prone to headaches,

24:24.196 --> 24:26.730
but now she chewing aspirin
like they breath mints.

24:26.732 --> 24:29.900
I mean, her whole life fell apart.

24:29.902 --> 24:32.069
But she chose not to
seek help for months.

24:32.071 --> 24:33.970
Well, maybe she just can't believe

24:33.972 --> 24:37.007
the man that she married
could ever hurt her.

24:37.009 --> 24:39.339
Hell, he's her husband.
She thinks she knows him.

24:39.341 --> 24:41.878
Yeah, sometimes you don't
know who you married to,

24:41.880 --> 24:43.780
and sometimes, they
don't want you to know.

24:45.184 --> 24:47.184
The truth eventually comes out, though.

24:48.220 --> 24:49.719
But maybe with this,

24:49.721 --> 24:51.522
it'll come out with your bullet.

24:51.524 --> 24:53.057
Hmm.

24:53.059 --> 24:55.259
Yeah.

24:55.261 --> 24:57.761
You know, the surgeon said

24:57.763 --> 24:59.896
that taking it out wasn't that hard.

24:59.898 --> 25:02.598
I mean, they were worried about
the location of the bullet,

25:02.600 --> 25:05.601
the risk of taking it
out, but as it turns out,

25:05.603 --> 25:07.503
she's just fine.

25:11.008 --> 25:12.608
Oh, Athena.

25:12.610 --> 25:14.343
Well, you know, now I finally know

25:14.345 --> 25:16.312
the motive of the groceries.

25:16.314 --> 25:20.983
Look, I am not having
this conversation again.

25:20.985 --> 25:23.519
I am not doing that surgery.

25:23.521 --> 25:24.853
So you're just gonna wait to die.

25:24.855 --> 25:28.057
I'm going through
another bout of radiation.

25:28.059 --> 25:30.793
The doctors put my name
on a list for a trial

25:30.795 --> 25:33.129
for this new chemotherapy pill.

25:33.131 --> 25:34.797
You know, it's showing some promise

25:34.799 --> 25:36.563
for shrinking tumors.

25:36.565 --> 25:39.401
- How much promise?
- Look, I know that you think...

25:39.403 --> 25:42.170
That you are a fool.

25:42.172 --> 25:44.439
Look, I wanna be supportive, Michael,

25:44.441 --> 25:46.775
I wanna respect your wishes, but...

25:50.514 --> 25:53.716
I do not want you to die.

25:53.718 --> 25:56.551
Me either. Okay?

26:05.395 --> 26:08.897
Oh, ballistics just came
back. They found a match.

26:08.899 --> 26:10.398
Does the gun belong to the husband?

26:10.400 --> 26:11.966
Worse.

26:11.968 --> 26:14.469
It belongs to the wife.

26:15.839 --> 26:17.405
Seem to be quite a few books.

26:17.407 --> 26:19.774
This was Victor's.

26:19.776 --> 26:22.710
His parents' medical library.

26:22.712 --> 26:25.380
And where is my
grandfather's private library?

26:25.382 --> 26:26.881
I don't know what you mean, sir.

26:26.883 --> 26:28.401
Well...

26:28.403 --> 26:31.461
Captain Frankenstein.

26:37.027 --> 26:38.960
Stay close to the candles.

26:38.962 --> 26:40.795
- Greg?
- You must be Josh.

26:40.797 --> 26:42.297
It's really nice to meet you.

26:42.299 --> 26:45.378
As first dates go, I gotta
admit you chose well.

26:45.380 --> 26:47.668
You know, you don't usually
think of the cemetery

26:47.670 --> 26:49.436
as a romantic place for a date,

26:49.438 --> 26:52.506
but it's quaint, kind of kitschy,

26:52.508 --> 26:53.707
and there are plenty of exits

26:53.709 --> 26:56.177
in case one of us turns
out to be too sketchy.

26:56.179 --> 26:59.736
I figure there is nothing more romantic

26:59.738 --> 27:03.651
than watching an old movie

27:03.653 --> 27:05.186
snacking on the graves

27:05.188 --> 27:07.221
of the people who used to make them.

27:07.223 --> 27:08.389
Thank you.

27:08.391 --> 27:11.124
If the zombies rise up, we'd be eaten

27:11.126 --> 27:13.627
by all the silver screen
starlets and screenwriters.

27:13.629 --> 27:15.629
I love it.

27:15.631 --> 27:16.730
Cheers.

27:16.732 --> 27:17.763
Cheers.

27:22.003 --> 27:24.704
Do you understand?

27:24.706 --> 27:26.206
I understand, I understand.

27:29.311 --> 27:33.012
And you like it there?
It's not too stressful?

27:33.014 --> 27:37.350
No, it's unbelievably stressful.

27:37.352 --> 27:40.253
But how many jobs can you
go home at the end of the day

27:40.255 --> 27:42.347
and feel like you've made a difference?

27:42.349 --> 27:45.139
I'll never be rich. I'll
never even be recognized.

27:45.141 --> 27:47.126
But I'll be...

27:47.128 --> 27:48.128
worthwhile.

27:50.064 --> 27:52.731
You know, I remember
when going to the movies

27:52.733 --> 27:54.733
was about making out in the back row.

27:56.069 --> 27:59.338
I heard Rudolph Valentino's
grave is somewhere around here.

27:59.340 --> 28:01.206
Maybe in the back row.

28:10.820 --> 28:13.585
This is exactly what I said
I wouldn't do on a first date.

28:13.587 --> 28:15.554
Oh, come on. This is the fun stuff.

28:15.556 --> 28:16.855
Took you long enough.

28:18.225 --> 28:19.391
Uh...

28:19.393 --> 28:21.245
okay, I don't know
what you guys are into,

28:21.247 --> 28:23.228
but it definitely doesn't
feel like my scene.

28:23.230 --> 28:25.166
You know, for somebody
who spends their days

28:25.168 --> 28:27.231
listening for clues,

28:27.233 --> 28:29.233
you sure managed to miss all of 'em.

28:32.639 --> 28:34.390
No. Please.

28:34.392 --> 28:36.222
Hey, I'm not the one who went online

28:36.224 --> 28:38.108
begging somebody to play me.

28:45.851 --> 28:48.786
Let's go.

28:48.788 --> 28:51.255
Hey, what's going on over there?

28:52.052 --> 28:54.052
_

29:07.828 --> 29:09.061
Oh, my God.

29:10.361 --> 29:11.517
Josh, are you okay?

29:11.519 --> 29:12.708
I'm okay.

29:12.710 --> 29:14.466
- What happened?
- I got jumped.

29:14.468 --> 29:16.769
They took my keys, my phone, my wallet,

29:16.771 --> 29:18.834
beat the crap out of me.

29:18.836 --> 29:20.068
For a minute there, I...

29:21.315 --> 29:23.315
I thought they were gonna kill me.

29:23.317 --> 29:25.317
Was this after your
date? The movie thing?

29:25.319 --> 29:27.485
It was my date.

29:27.487 --> 29:30.127
- He was the one.
- Oh, God, I'm so sorry.

29:30.129 --> 29:31.218
He set me up.

29:31.220 --> 29:34.860
Him and his friend. I
never even saw it coming.

29:34.862 --> 29:36.294
I am an idiot.

29:37.497 --> 29:39.331
I thought he was sweet.

29:39.333 --> 29:41.333
- That he liked me.
- No.

29:41.335 --> 29:43.401
You just trusted the wrong person.

29:43.403 --> 29:45.169
Mr. Russo?

29:46.940 --> 29:49.173
We had officers canvass the cemetery.

29:49.175 --> 29:50.612
There's still no sign of your phone,

29:50.614 --> 29:52.944
but they recovered your
keys and your wallet.

29:52.946 --> 29:54.779
I'm afraid the cash was gone though.

29:54.781 --> 29:56.047
At least they saved me the hassle

29:56.049 --> 29:58.717
of replacing all my
credit cards and IDs.

29:58.719 --> 30:00.652
You can pick up
your things at the station.

30:00.654 --> 30:02.804
A detective will take
your formal statement then.

30:02.806 --> 30:04.656
Does that have to happen tonight?

30:04.658 --> 30:05.824
I'm just really worn out.

30:05.826 --> 30:08.292
Well, you know what? You can
just stay with me tonight

30:08.294 --> 30:09.969
and I'll drive you to the
station in the morning.

30:09.971 --> 30:12.364
Of course. Tomorrow is fine.

30:12.366 --> 30:14.565
Are you sure you didn't
recognize either man?

30:14.567 --> 30:15.995
No identifiable features?

30:15.997 --> 30:18.369
No. Sorry.

30:18.371 --> 30:19.570
Look, we'll do our best,

30:19.572 --> 30:21.705
but I need to set your expectations.

30:21.707 --> 30:23.540
No, I know the drill.

30:23.542 --> 30:25.376
If it's okay, I'd
like to get out of here

30:25.378 --> 30:28.144
and just put this whole night behind me.

30:29.281 --> 30:30.714
Call us if you think of anything else.

30:30.716 --> 30:32.215
Thanks.

30:34.453 --> 30:37.621
- Josh.
- I already feel like a fool.

30:37.623 --> 30:39.990
I don't need the rest of
the world in on the joke.

30:41.427 --> 30:42.427
Okay.

30:52.404 --> 30:54.670
- Nothing?
- No sign of the gun.

30:54.672 --> 30:56.238
Or any gun.

30:56.240 --> 30:59.074
No ammunition, no
gunshot residue, no blood.

30:59.076 --> 31:00.242
The house is immaculate.

31:00.244 --> 31:01.577
Ha!

31:05.116 --> 31:07.717
Ma'am? Hi, LAPD.

31:07.719 --> 31:09.151
May we speak to you a moment?

31:09.153 --> 31:11.353
I don't see why not. Just
doing a little yard work.

31:11.355 --> 31:13.789
Yes, Detective Romero was remarking

31:13.791 --> 31:16.024
