31:16.026 --> 31:18.198
Being out here does
take up most of my day.

31:18.200 --> 31:21.191
Oh, I'm sure you see everything
that goes on around here.

31:21.193 --> 31:24.384
I am also the president
of our neighborhood watch.

31:24.386 --> 31:26.809
I take that responsibility
very seriously.

31:26.811 --> 31:28.011
Mm.

31:28.013 --> 31:29.604
How well do you know the Wallaces?

31:29.606 --> 31:33.007
We wave occasionally.
I always liked Joan.

31:33.009 --> 31:34.609
Never that sure about Henry.

31:34.611 --> 31:38.279
Then he retired, and I finally
was able to make up my mind.

31:38.281 --> 31:40.248
I don't like the man.

31:40.250 --> 31:42.984
Between you and me, I'm
not sure Joan does either.

31:42.986 --> 31:44.486
They weren't getting along?

31:44.488 --> 31:47.855
You know, people used to retire at 65

31:47.857 --> 31:50.758
back when life expectancy was 68.

31:50.760 --> 31:53.227
Now, it's all early retirement

31:53.229 --> 31:55.129
and late life divorce.

31:56.132 --> 31:58.399
I'm sorry, but I don't understand

31:58.401 --> 32:01.369
what any of this has
to do with the break-in.

32:01.371 --> 32:03.537
Someone broke into their home?

32:03.539 --> 32:05.773
I assumed that was
why you all were here.

32:05.775 --> 32:09.143
Though honestly, you are
a little late to the party.

32:09.145 --> 32:12.513
That must've been three months ago.

32:12.515 --> 32:14.983
Did the Wallaces tell
you they'd had a break-in?

32:14.985 --> 32:17.485
No. Their contractor did.

32:19.155 --> 32:20.921
That window there was replaced.

32:20.923 --> 32:24.324
The contractor hauled away
some furniture and a rug,

32:24.326 --> 32:26.227
a bunch of Christmas decorations.

32:26.229 --> 32:28.996
Said he painted and
redid the floors too.

32:28.998 --> 32:30.663
Redecorating the crime scene?

32:30.665 --> 32:32.899
That's why we couldn't find anything.

32:32.901 --> 32:34.901
Didn't see Joan or Henry for weeks.

32:34.903 --> 32:36.336
They were out of town.

32:36.338 --> 32:38.338
Do you remember when
all of this happened?

32:39.816 --> 32:41.306
January 11th.

32:41.308 --> 32:43.131
Would you like the
contractor's information?

32:43.133 --> 32:45.823
Yes. Then I'd like to hug you.

32:48.351 --> 32:51.018
I think it'd be best if
Mr. Wallace stepped outside.

32:51.020 --> 32:53.686
That's silly. Henry should stay.

32:53.688 --> 32:56.155
My memory is terrible.
Maybe he can help.

32:57.258 --> 32:59.458
You can have this back. We made a copy.

32:59.460 --> 33:00.692
Thanks.

33:00.694 --> 33:03.129
I was wondering where that had got to.

33:03.131 --> 33:04.698
When we were looking through it,

33:04.700 --> 33:06.956
we noticed that there
didn't seem to be any entries

33:06.958 --> 33:10.002
about your trip, or
the living room remodel.

33:11.506 --> 33:13.539
Did we remodel the living room?

33:14.909 --> 33:18.210
No, that's right. We did.

33:20.048 --> 33:24.150
I just don't remember why, though.

33:24.152 --> 33:26.318
We just finished the house last year.

33:27.588 --> 33:30.622
Why did we redo the living room?

33:30.624 --> 33:33.225
Do you remember what
happened on January 11th?

33:34.395 --> 33:37.364
Maybe you were taking
down Christmas decorations?

33:37.366 --> 33:40.577
No, we always take those
down right after New Year's.

33:49.076 --> 33:51.643
Henry, what happened to that rug?

33:51.645 --> 33:55.280
Oh, I loved that rug.

33:55.282 --> 33:57.115
Why did we replace it?

33:58.285 --> 33:59.918
There was an accident.

34:07.661 --> 34:09.359
Henry...

34:12.297 --> 34:13.998
What did you do?

34:19.072 --> 34:20.771
What did you do?

34:27.112 --> 34:29.614
I thought you were gonna take
down those wreaths for me.

34:29.616 --> 34:31.782
- In a minute.
- No more minutes.

34:31.784 --> 34:33.985
We should've put all
this stuff away last week.

34:33.987 --> 34:36.152
What happens if we don't?

34:36.155 --> 34:37.931
Does the world come screeching to a halt

34:37.933 --> 34:41.025
because the wreaths are up past MLK Day?

34:41.027 --> 34:42.826
I don't know why you're like this.

34:42.828 --> 34:45.629
I miss when you used
to work for a living.

34:45.630 --> 34:48.532
Yeah, well, you've never
worked a day in your life.

34:48.534 --> 34:49.899
Oh, the hell I haven't.

34:49.900 --> 34:51.541
I have taken care of this house

34:51.543 --> 34:54.170
and I've taken care of
you for the last 30 years,

34:54.172 --> 34:55.772
and all I ask is that you...

34:55.774 --> 34:56.867
And all you have asked

34:56.869 --> 34:59.042
is that I work 60-plus hours a week

34:59.044 --> 35:01.311
to support you and this house

35:01.313 --> 35:04.281
and whatever ridiculously
expensive hobby

35:04.283 --> 35:05.315
your heart desires.

35:05.317 --> 35:07.618
Ceramics class?

35:07.620 --> 35:10.154
Henry, what did you do?

35:10.156 --> 35:11.821
Do you know how hard I worked on that?

35:11.823 --> 35:13.322
No, but I know how much it cost me

35:13.324 --> 35:14.990
for you to learn how to make something

35:14.992 --> 35:17.126
that I could buy for 20 bucks!

35:17.128 --> 35:18.461
Glass-blowing lessons!

35:20.998 --> 35:22.365
What are you doing?

35:22.367 --> 35:24.066
This is my time!

35:24.068 --> 35:25.601
My retirement!

35:25.603 --> 35:28.571
And I'm not gonna let you
rule my golden damn years

35:28.573 --> 35:30.473
the way you rule the
rest of my damn life.

35:39.284 --> 35:40.416
Fine.

35:44.454 --> 35:47.522
I will deal with the decorations myself.

35:49.059 --> 35:52.227
I always thought when you retired,

35:52.229 --> 35:54.829
it would be our time.

35:54.831 --> 35:57.165
Our time together.

35:59.203 --> 36:01.069
I know you're upset about something,

36:01.071 --> 36:02.904
but I'm your wife,

36:02.906 --> 36:04.372
so you're stuck with me.

36:22.191 --> 36:23.490
You shot me.

36:26.161 --> 36:28.397
I don't know what came over me.

36:28.399 --> 36:31.332
The thought of 30 more years
in that house with you, and I...

36:34.604 --> 36:36.937
Call it temporary insanity.

36:36.939 --> 36:38.606
Well, you are certainly
within your rights

36:38.608 --> 36:40.307
to make that case to a judge.

36:40.309 --> 36:41.808
I'm sorry, Joanie.

36:41.810 --> 36:44.745
I regretted it immediately
after I did it.

36:44.747 --> 36:47.306
I tried to make it up
to you as best I could.

36:47.308 --> 36:48.330
After.

36:48.332 --> 36:50.183
You lied to me.

36:50.185 --> 36:53.119
All this time, you knew
what was wrong with me,

36:53.121 --> 36:56.456
and you kept telling me
it was all in my head.

36:56.458 --> 36:58.658
Well, I guess it was,

36:58.660 --> 37:00.360
because you put it there.

37:05.316 --> 37:07.150
Now, you're gonna be okay.

37:08.270 --> 37:10.570
He played me for a fool.

37:10.572 --> 37:14.307
And you just showed
him that he was wrong.

37:21.198 --> 37:23.181
Chris. Come on, buddy.

37:23.183 --> 37:25.350
Eat something before school.

37:25.352 --> 37:27.352
I don't feel well.

37:28.589 --> 37:31.023
You sick?

37:31.025 --> 37:32.190
Hmm.

37:33.628 --> 37:35.684
You sure?

37:35.686 --> 37:36.762
I don't wanna go.

37:36.764 --> 37:39.131
Okay.

37:45.639 --> 37:47.672
You still upset about the other day?

37:47.674 --> 37:51.209
I just wanna be like everyone else.

37:51.211 --> 37:52.310
I know.

37:54.181 --> 37:56.214
But you're not.

37:56.216 --> 37:58.416
I know I told you you can do anything,

37:58.418 --> 38:01.419
and that was a dumb thing for me to say.

38:01.421 --> 38:03.021
Because I have CP.

38:03.023 --> 38:04.356
No.

38:04.358 --> 38:05.557
Because...

38:07.227 --> 38:09.427
Nobody can do everything.

38:10.564 --> 38:12.897
And yes,

38:12.899 --> 38:14.104
there are things in life

38:14.106 --> 38:15.973
that you're not gonna be able to do.

38:17.504 --> 38:19.937
And there's other stuff that
you are gonna be able to do,

38:19.939 --> 38:23.141
but it's gonna be a lot harder
than it is for the other kids

38:23.143 --> 38:24.575
because you have CP.

38:24.577 --> 38:28.245
I'm sorry. I won't skateboard again.

38:28.247 --> 38:30.414
It's not about the skateboarding.

38:31.584 --> 38:33.685
I just don't want you to be scared.

38:35.421 --> 38:37.955
You tried something,
and it didn't work out.

38:37.957 --> 38:39.523
Maybe the next time it does.

38:39.525 --> 38:42.060
But you can skateboard.

38:42.062 --> 38:43.294
You know what I can't do?

38:43.296 --> 38:46.164
Cook?

38:46.166 --> 38:48.465
Hey, that's not nice.

38:48.467 --> 38:51.435
But probably true.

38:51.437 --> 38:53.104
I have black thumb.

38:53.106 --> 38:55.807
I've killed every plant
that's ever been given to me.

38:55.809 --> 38:57.974
But your science teacher told me

38:57.976 --> 39:00.377
that you did the best job

39:00.379 --> 39:01.679
out of your whole class

39:01.681 --> 39:04.481
growing plants from seeds,

39:04.483 --> 39:06.116
so there's something
you're better at than me.

39:06.118 --> 39:07.618
- Really?
- Really.

39:09.255 --> 39:12.289
I don't want you to ever stop trying.

39:12.291 --> 39:14.458
But maybe...

39:14.460 --> 39:15.759
until you get a little older,

39:15.761 --> 39:18.262
maybe we try new things together, okay?

39:18.264 --> 39:19.830
Okay.

39:21.634 --> 39:23.367
You're not like any other kid.

39:23.369 --> 39:25.769
You're my kid.

39:25.771 --> 39:28.305
I love you more than
anything in this world.

39:28.307 --> 39:29.973
I love you too, Dad.

39:29.975 --> 39:31.841
Aw. Mwah.

39:37.582 --> 39:38.948
Sorry, is this a bad time?

39:38.950 --> 39:40.116
Mr. Diaz.

39:40.118 --> 39:41.718
Eddie.

39:41.720 --> 39:43.453
Please.

39:43.455 --> 39:45.855
I wanted to apologize for the other day.

39:45.857 --> 39:48.625
I was out of line and
you didn't deserve that.

39:48.627 --> 39:50.560
You had every right to be upset.

39:50.562 --> 39:52.228
It's my job to look after your son

39:52.230 --> 39:54.297
and I failed to do that.

39:54.299 --> 39:56.499
I'm just relieved Christopher is okay.

39:56.501 --> 39:58.324
Yeah, I fight so hard
to try and protect him,

39:58.326 --> 40:00.136
I forget falling down is a part of life.

40:00.138 --> 40:02.037
It's supposed to teach us
how to get back up, right?

40:02.039 --> 40:03.161
Yes.

40:03.163 --> 40:05.340
There's a lot to be said for
getting back on the horse,

40:05.342 --> 40:06.877
but there's also some value

40:06.879 --> 40:08.744
in learning that you don't like horses.

40:08.746 --> 40:10.579
I'm sorry?

40:10.581 --> 40:14.616
Sometimes, our limitations
tell us when to stop.

40:14.618 --> 40:17.919
But sometimes, they can
show us where to look next.

40:17.921 --> 40:20.422
Today, he falls off the skateboard.

40:20.424 --> 40:22.824
But tomorrow, he writes
the great American novel.

40:24.127 --> 40:26.227
I know you said he was
doing good in class, but...

40:27.431 --> 40:30.031
Okay, maybe not tomorrow, but...

40:30.033 --> 40:31.266
Someday.

40:31.268 --> 40:32.934
Yeah.

40:32.936 --> 40:34.102
Someday.

40:38.574 --> 40:41.876
Welcome back!

40:41.878 --> 40:43.011
Thank you.

40:43.013 --> 40:44.666
If I'd known I'd get
this much attention,

40:44.668 --> 40:45.948
I would've gotten mugged sooner.

40:47.217 --> 40:48.516
Hi.

40:48.518 --> 40:50.084
- Ah, there he is.
- Good to see you, thanks.

40:50.086 --> 40:51.719
- Hey, welcome back, Josh.
- Good to see you.

40:51.721 --> 40:53.922
- Thanks.
- Josh, you're back!

40:53.924 --> 40:55.589
Okay.

40:56.726 --> 40:59.060
You didn't tell them. Thanks.

40:59.062 --> 41:01.395
You asked me not. I'm
still not sure why.

41:01.397 --> 41:03.698
- This was not your fault.
- I should've known better.

41:03.700 --> 41:05.666
It's not too late to
go back to the police.

41:05.668 --> 41:07.637
You know, I tried to
pull up his profile,

41:07.639 --> 41:09.729
get a copy of his photo, but it's gone.

41:09.731 --> 41:12.640
Completely scrubbed.
It was a total scam.

41:12.642 --> 41:15.042
Yeah, that probably
means he's done it before.

41:15.044 --> 41:16.794
If you could get them
a description of him,

41:16.796 --> 41:18.713
maybe they could find him.

41:18.715 --> 41:20.914
- I mean, he hurt you.
- Bruises are healing.

41:20.916 --> 41:24.017
The humiliation, that's a
little harder to get over.

41:24.019 --> 41:25.553
And to have it written
down in some report

41:25.555 --> 41:27.321
for strangers to see?

41:27.323 --> 41:29.089
I can't, Maddie.

41:29.091 --> 41:31.091
So what, you're just gonna
act like it didn't happen?

41:31.093 --> 41:32.125
No, I'm not.

41:32.127 --> 41:34.094
I'll deal with it.

41:34.096 --> 41:35.463
In my own way.

41:47.642 --> 41:49.709
9-1-1. What's your emergency?

41:51.513 --> 41:53.112
And can I get your location?

41:55.283 --> 41:57.684
Okay.

42:00.489 --> 42:02.121
- Nice.
- Yeah.

42:24.979 --> 42:26.946
Thought you could use some carbs.

42:36.925 --> 42:39.125
Dad,

42:39.127 --> 42:40.492
I don't wanna be here.

42:40.494 --> 42:41.560
Trust me, it'll be fun.

42:41.562 --> 42:43.329
Hey, Chris!

42:43.331 --> 42:45.965
Surprise!

42:45.967 --> 42:48.100
- What's that?
- Hey, remember when I told you

42:48.102 --> 42:50.402
that if you wanted to try something new,

42:50.404 --> 42:51.970
we should try it together?

42:51.972 --> 42:53.338
Yeah.

42:53.340 --> 42:54.673
Let's try skateboarding.

42:54.675 --> 42:56.341
- Okay.
- Okay!

42:57.978 --> 42:59.177
Ready to ride?

42:59.179 --> 43:00.278
Ready!

43:00.280 --> 43:02.614
Away we go.

